{"id":1295184619,"question_id":43,"lang":"java","lang_name":"Java","time":"4 days, 22 hours","timestamp":1718940548,"status":10,"status_display":"Accepted","runtime":"2 ms","url":"/submissions/detail/1295184619/","is_pending":"Not Pending","title":"Multiply Strings","memory":"41.5 MB","code":"class Solution {\n    public String multiply(String num1, String num2) {\n        if(num1.equals(\"0\") || num2.equals(\"0\"))\n            return \"0\";\n\n        int n1 = num1.length();\n        int n2 = num2.length();\n\n        int[] prod = new int[n1+n2-1];\n        \n        for(int i=0;i<n1;i++){\n            for(int j = 0;j<n2;j++){\n                prod[i+j]+=(num1.charAt(i)-'0')*(num2.charAt(j)-'0');\n            }\n        }\n\n        for(int i=prod.length-1;i>0;i--){\n            prod[i-1]+=prod[i]/10;\n            prod[i]%=10;\n        }\n\n        StringBuilder sb = new StringBuilder();\n        for(int n:prod)\n            sb.append(n);\n\n        return sb.toString();\n    }\n}","compare_result":"","title_slug":"multiply-strings","has_notes":false,"flag_type":1}
